Research Question:

How long did the recovery of the housing market take in the US after the 2007 market crash? How have prices changed since then? Could there be another bubble burst coming soon?

This shows the average house price across the US

Avgdata <- Saleprices %>% filter(RegionID==102001)
newAvgdata <- Avgdata %>% gather(month, price, -RegionID, -RegionName, -SizeRank)

newAvgdata %>%
  mutate(Year = lubridate::dym(month)) %>%
  ggplot(aes(x=Year,y=price))+geom_line()

Adds a new max, min, and mean column for the price of all the homes at that location.

Justmonths <- Saleprices[-c(1,2,3)]
Meanarr <- apply(Justmonths,1,mean,na.rm=TRUE)
Maxarr <- apply(Justmonths,1,max,na.rm=TRUE)
Minarr <- apply(Justmonths,1,min,na.rm=TRUE)
Saleprices <- 
  Saleprices %>%
  mutate(MeanPrice = Meanarr) %>%
  mutate(MaximumPrice = Maxarr) %>%
  mutate(MinimumPrice = Minarr)
